question_title: Will the community prediction be higher than 30.00% on 2026-02-11 for the Metaculus question "Will Benjamin Netanyahu cease to be Prime Minister of Israel during 2026?"?
summary: This meta-prediction asks whether the Metaculus CP for "Will Netanyahu cease to be PM in 2026?" will exceed 30% on Feb 11. The CP is currently at 26% (down from 30% at launch on Feb 1), meaning it needs to gain 4+ percentage points in 7 days. With 787 forecasters creating significant inertia and a recent downward trend, this reversal seems unlikely without a major catalyst. The gap between Manifold markets (39-44%) and Metaculus (26%) creates some upward pressure, but this gap has existed while CP dropped. Phase 2 ceasefire negotiations starting Feb 4 could generate news that stresses Netanyahu's coalition, but even coalition tensions don't guarantee a CP swing of this magnitude in one week.

factors.description: CP has dropped from 30% to 26% in 3 days - recent trend is clearly downward, not toward the threshold
787 forecasters creates significant inertia - large bases resist rapid movement without major news
Manifold markets at 39-44% vs Metaculus 26% - significant gap could drive cross-platform convergence upward
Phase 2 ceasefire negotiations starting Feb 4 could generate coalition-stressing news (Smotrich threatening to leave)
No immediate coalition collapse - despite fragility, government is currently holding
